  'ielts,letter,task1,gt',
  E'["Dear Sir or Madam,\\nI am writing to inquire about your exclusive seminar hall that we are planning to reserve for an official event. We are expecting a few additional amenities in order to accommodate the event without any intervention and to make it a success.\\nWe will organise the annual get-together party and I would like to know the availability of your seminar hall during the second week of next March. Our agenda will be a staff meet-up followed by an hour-long presentation and it would conclude with a grand dinner party. We would require a high-resolution LCD projector and a Wi-Fi connection facility for Laptops. The seating arrangement is expected to be for almost 100 people. We also require facilities for welcome drinks for guests and dinner for all of them.\\nI am curious to know about the rates to hire the hall for 6 hours, from 4:00 pm to 10:00 pm, with the list of facilities it offers. Additionally, please send me the menu for dinner including drinks. Also, mention the best possible concession you can offer and break down the expected expenses. We will not compromise the hygienic and food quality and we are expecting the party to be organised without any glaring issue from your end.\\nI look forward to hearing from you soon.\\nYours faithfully,\\nMohammed Abu\\n[", "Dear Sir or Madam,\\nI am writing to inquire about the availability of your party centre for an executive event. I work for the Robinsons & Brothers, and we are planning to organise an exclusive event on December 17, 2025. I would like to obtain some information to reserve the venue.\\nFirst, we are planning for an event where approximately 80 people would be present. We need to hire the venue for the whole day and you would be responsible for serving welcome drinks and lunch to the guests. Some of our guests would bring their parents who are senior citizens and might be physically challenged. What arrangements do you have for such people? Please include some Thai and Chinese dishes on the lunch menu.\\nI would like to get a confirmation if the venue is available for the mentioned date and how much it would cost us to reserve it. You can send me the information, including the menu and details price list, via fax using the number 27-01-25412014 or email me at\\nThis email address is being protected from spambots. You need JavaScript enabled to view it.\\n. I am confident that you can provide us with the best possible service we need based on the abundance of positive reviews you have.\\nYours faithfully,\\nTiffany Lace", "Dear Sir or Madam,\\nI am writing to request some information to reserve your venue for an executive event for Dreko Company Limited. We will organise the annual board meeting in December for the company stakeholders and investors and expecting your response to finalise the location.\\nFirstly, I would like to know the availability of the venue at the end of June 2025. We need the venue for the whole day and 27th June is our preference for the event. Secondly, a light breakfast during the meeting is expected to be served and dinner should be arranged following the meeting. Finally, please inform me of the cost for all the above-mentioned arrangements. Also, do let me know if we can avail any discounts for that.\\nWe are expecting around 30 guests and would really appreciate it if you could provide all these details before the end of this week.\\nThank you in advance. Looking forward to hearing from you soon.\\nYours faithfully,\\nRiya Nagpal\\n[", "Dear Sir or Madam,\\nI am writing to inform you that we are considering your banquet hall for our annual dinner party that we are planning to organise at the end of October 2025. Therefore, I would like to obtain some information to finalise the process of reserving this venue.\\nFirst of all, please notify me of the availability of the venue as per our schedule. Can we avail of it on the evening of 28th or 29th October? I would also like to know about the service you offer including the dinner menu, power backup and decoration. As it is a prestigious event for our company, you should follow some decent theme for the decoration and provide a buffet menu. My recommendation is to use a professional interior decorator and use white flowers and colourful balloons for the decoration.\\nFinally, please forward me the estimated expenses that will incur to hire the venue and avail the services. Send it to my email address -\\nThis email address is being protected from spambots. You need JavaScript enabled to view it.\\n. Previous experience with your company was outstanding but this time, I am expecting more innovative design and high quality of services.\\nYours faithfully,\\nFahad Sultan\\n[", "Dear Sir/Madam,I am writing this letter to inquire about booking the dining hall, which we plan on using for an office party. It is going to be a gathering of people from multiple projects. We are planning to organize the event either on 27th August or 1st September, depending upon the confirmation received from the projects.Before proposing a complete plan for the teams, I would like to collect some information.Firstly, I would like to know if the hall is available on the mentioned dates. We are going to kick start the event in the evening, however, we would like to book the hall from the afternoon. Secondly, we would have some team activities which includes an Ice breaking session and a dance night. We would like to arrange a DJ and a dance floor for the evening as well. If there is an option, we would like to arrange a dance floor and fun activities in the same hall. Thirdly, we are expecting a turnout of 400 people. Considering the number of people, we would like to arrange the buffet for both Veg and Non-Veg category.Please send a quotation with details and costs mentioned for each activity separately, it will help us to plan the event better. Awaiting revert from your end.Yours faithfully,\\nReply\\nQuote\\nHarpreet Kaur\\n8 years 5 months\\nAll these", "s are over the limit for word count. Doesn''t it affect your band?\\nReply\\nQuote\\nPranay Jar\\n8 years 5 months\\nI want to get letter sample about to work in a club for flower decoration.\\nReply\\nQuote\\nJoe Anne Wills\\n8 years 11 months\\nHi, Suppose I want to ask someone to host a high school party for free?\\nReply\\nQuote\\nSaroj\\n9 years 6 months\\nHi,Suppose I want to organize a blood donation camp at my company and I want to inform all the customers, employees and share holders for this event. In this case what type of letter will be preferable? Please mention with an example.\\nReply\\nQuote\\nSam G\\n9 years 11 months\\nQuestion for the site admin/moderator - If in the real IELTS test, I write the same level of your", ", what band score they will grant? Thanks for your big effort.\\nReply\\nQuote\\nSudip Pant\\n10 years 4 months\\nDear Sir,I am writing this letter to request you to book a hall for an event on the date of 23rd June. The event will be organised for staffs as a get-together program. I need details of your hotel''s facilities, whether breakfast and dinner are inclusive of the cost or not and way of paying. I also expect to get some concession on booking your hall. We will be there for almost 6 hours. First hour would be the welcoming hour and breakfast for the all the staffs. In the second hour we will formally start our program and for this, we need a projector with a big LCD. There will be 110 people in total.I am so curious to know what will be there as special items in breakfast as well as in dinner. If you can send me the menu for that day, it will be better. We need dinner with drinks as well and facility to drop-off every employee.Please send details via reply email including your rate, schedule and availability of the venue.I look forward to hearing your response soon.Thank you,With RegardsSudip Pant\\nReply\\nQuote\\nIELTS Mentor\\n11 years\\nAkash, we have changed the name from Marcio to ''Tiffany''. Both names should be same unless she is using her nickname at the top and full name at the bottom of the letter.\\nReply\\nQuote\\nAkash\\n11 years\\nHi, just want to ask, In the letter above, the author started with \\"My name is Marcio\\" and while closing he/she wrote \\"Yours faithfully, Tiffany Lace \\", is this valid?\\nReply\\nQuote\\n√ó\\nReport\\nReport\\nClose"]'::jsonb,
